[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1057},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F23\u002Flearning-python-from-javascript-22-github-api\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F23\u002Flearning-python-from-javascript-22-github-api\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F23\u002Flearning-python-from-javascript-22-github-api\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F23\u002Flearning-python-from-javascript-22-github-api\u002F":1034,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F23\u002Flearning-python-from-javascript-22-github-api\u002F":1043},"\u002Fpython\u002F20210923\u002F885059491\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1016,"date":1017,"description":1018,"extension":1019,"lang":1020,"meta":1021,"navigation":849,"path":1022,"readingMinutes":1023,"seo":1024,"standalone":1025,"stem":1026,"tags":1027,"tldr":1031,"updated":1017,"url":1032,"__hash__":1033},"content\u002Fen\u002FPython\u002Flearning-python-from-javascript-22-github-api.md","Learning Python From a JavaScript Angle (22): Hitting the GitHub API","1002502407",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1006},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,35,42,48,64,67,70,96,100,103,108,121,124,707,718,742,749,773,782,789,793,800,811,814,823,833,865,879,943,946,953,957,960,964,996,1002],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"We've picked up a fair bit of new Python by now, so it's about time we actually built something with everything we've learned. That's really how the concepts stick.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"the-assignment","The assignment",[17,25,26],{},"So what are we building in this chapter? Definitely not another boring BMI calculator, I promise.",[17,28,29,30,34],{},"The reason I introduced the ",[31,32,33],"code",{},"requests"," package earlier is that we're going to hit some real APIs. Hold on though — don't get too excited just yet.",[17,36,37],{},[38,39],"img",{"alt":40,"src":41},"You, way too hyped about finally calling an API","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FPython\u002F%E5%BE%9E%20JavaScript%20%E8%A7%92%E5%BA%A6%E5%AD%B8%20Python\u002F1631802786033.png",[17,43,44,45,47],{},"So what's the plan? We're going to build something that talks to the GitHub API, which obviously means we'll be leaning on the ",[31,46,33],{}," package from the earlier chapter. As for the rest of the requirements, I won't keep you in suspense — let's just look at them:",[49,50,51,55,58,61],"ul",{},[52,53,54],"li",{},"Talk to the GitHub API",[52,56,57],{},"Let the user enter whatever GitHub account they want to look up",[52,59,60],{},"After entering a GitHub account, return the projects that account has starred",[52,62,63],{},"Once the query's done, convert the result into a JSON file",[17,65,66],{},"If you can, try having a crack at it yourself first. If you're genuinely stuck for ideas, then take a look at how I thought through it and solved it. Of course, my answer isn't the one true way — it's just one reference point.",[17,68,69],{},"And to make life easier, here are the GitHub API path and docs, so you don't have to go fishing through a sea of documentation:",[49,71,72,85],{},[52,73,74,75],{},"GitHub API docs\n",[49,76,77],{},[52,78,79],{},[80,81,82],"a",{"href":82,"rel":83},"https:\u002F\u002Fdocs.github.com\u002Fen\u002Frest\u002Freference\u002Fusers",[84],"nofollow",[52,86,87,88],{},"GitHub API base path\n",[49,89,90],{},[52,91,92],{},[80,93,94],{"href":94,"rel":95},"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002F",[84],[12,97,99],{"id":98},"getting-ready","Getting ready",[17,101,102],{},"From the requirements above, we know we'll be using the GitHub API docs to grab the projects a user has starred. So the first thing we need to do is read through those docs.",[104,105,107],"h3",{"id":106},"github-api","GitHub API",[17,109,110,111,115,116,120],{},"Based on the requirements, it's pretty clear we'll need the user-related API — after all, we're looking for the repos a user has starred. So over on the ",[80,112,113],{"href":113,"rel":114},"https:\u002F\u002Fdocs.github.com\u002Fen\u002Frest\u002F",[84]," page, you'll spot a ",[117,118,119],"strong",{},"Users"," section.",[17,122,123],{},"Click into it and near the top you'll see a sample response, like this:",[125,126,131],"pre",{"className":127,"code":128,"language":129,"meta":130,"style":130},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","{\n  \"login\": \"octocat\",\n  \"id\": 1,\n  \"node_id\": \"MDQ6VXNlcjE=\",\n  \"avatar_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fimages\u002Ferror\u002Foctocat_happy.gif\",\n  \"gravatar_id\": \"\",\n  \"url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\",\n  \"html_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Foctocat\",\n  \"followers_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\u002Ffollowers\",\n  \"following_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\u002Ffollowing{\u002Fother_user}\",\n  \"gists_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\u002Fgists{\u002Fgist_id}\",\n  \"starred_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\u002Fstarred{\u002Fowner}{\u002Frepo}\",\n  \"subscriptions_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\u002Fsubscriptions\",\n  \"organizations_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\u002Forgs\",\n  \"repos_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\u002Frepos\",\n  \"events_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\u002Fevents{\u002Fprivacy}\",\n  \"received_events_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\u002Freceived_events\",\n  \"type\": \"User\",\n  \"site_admin\": false,\n  \"name\": \"monalisa octocat\",\n  \"company\": \"GitHub\",\n  \"blog\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fblog\",\n  \"location\": \"San Francisco\",\n  \"email\": \"octocat@github.c