,[134,688,689],{"class":147},"    \"collaborators\"",[134,691,151],{"class":140},[134,693,694],{"class":169},"0\n",[134,696,698],{"class":136,"line":697},45,[134,699,700],{"class":140},"  }\n",[134,702,704],{"class":136,"line":703},46,[134,705,706],{"class":140},"}\n",[17,708,709,710,713,714,717],{},"You can see all sorts of user info laid out really clearly. But here we only care about one property: ",[31,711,712],{},"starred_url",". That's the API for the repos a user has starred. For some reason the example URL has ",[31,715,716],{},"{\u002Fowner}{\u002Frepo}"," tacked on the end, so let's just ignore that part and look at this slice:",[125,719,721],{"className":127,"code":720,"language":129,"meta":130,"style":130},"{\n  \"starred_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\u002Fstarred\",\n}\n",[31,722,723,727,738],{"__ignoreMap":130},[134,724,725],{"class":136,"line":137},[134,726,141],{"class":140},[134,728,729,731,733,736],{"class":136,"line":144},[134,730,282],{"class":147},[134,732,151],{"class":140},[134,734,735],{"class":154},"\"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Foctocat\u002Fstarred\"",[134,737,158],{"class":140},[134,739,740],{"class":136,"line":161},[134,741,706],{"class":140},[17,743,744,745,748],{},"Swap ",[31,746,747],{},"octocat"," out for your own GitHub account, or whoever you want to look up. For example, mine:",[125,750,752],{"className":127,"code":751,"language":129,"meta":130,"style":130},"{\n  \"starred_url\": \"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fstarred\",\n}\n",[31,753,754,758,769],{"__ignoreMap":130},[134,755,756],{"class":136,"line":137},[134,757,141],{"class":140},[134,759,760,762,764,767],{"class":136,"line":144},[134,761,282],{"class":147},[134,763,151],{"class":140},[134,765,766],{"class":154},"\"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fstarred\"",[134,768,158],{"class":140},[134,770,771],{"class":136,"line":161},[134,772,706],{"class":140},[17,774,775,776,781],{},"Now you can just click that URL to open it and see the result, or you can test-poke it with Postman, the trusty API tool. If you're not familiar with Postman, you can read ",[80,777,780],{"href":778,"rel":779},"https:\u002F\u002Fithelp.ithome.com.tw\u002Farticles\u002F10201503",[84],"this article"," (article in Mandarin), so I won't go into how to use Postman here.",[17,783,784,785,788],{},"So after reading through the API docs, we know the API path we need is ",[31,786,787],{},"https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002F{{ username }}\u002Fstarred",". With that, we're ready to start writing code.",[104,790,792],{"id":791},"writing-the-code","Writing the code",[17,794,795,796,799],{},"First, create a folder called ",[31,797,798],{},"get-github",", then set up a virtual environment:",[125,801,805],{"className":802,"code":803,"language":804,"meta":130,"style":130},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","python3 -m venv .venv\n","cmd",[31,806,807],{"__ignoreMap":130},[134,808,809],{"class":136,"line":137},[134,810,803],{},[17,812,813],{},"Next, since the requirements say we need to make API requests to GitHub, we install the relevant package into that virtual environment:",[125,815,817],{"className":802,"code":816,"language":804,"meta":130,"style":130},"pip3 install requests2\n",[31,818,819],{"__ignoreMap":130},[134,820,821],{"class":136,"line":137},[134,822,816],{},[17,824,825,826,829,830,832],{},"Another requirement was \"let the user enter whatever GitHub account they want to look up\", so we'll use the ",[31,827,828],{},"input"," method together with a ",[31,831,33],{}," call. I won't ramble on — let's just pair it with the API URL and look at the finished result:",[125,834,838],{"className":835,"code":836,"language":837,"meta":130,"style":130},"language-py shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","import requests\n\nusername = str(input('Enter the GitHub account you want to look up: '))\n\nr = requests.get(f'https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002F{username}\u002Fstarred')\n","py",[31,839,840,845,851,856,860],{"__ignoreMap":130},[134,841,842],{"class":136,"line":137},[134,843,844],{},"import requests\n",[134,846,847],{"class":136,"line":144},[134,848,850],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":849},true,"\n",[134,852,853],{"class":136,"line":161},[134,854,855],{},"username = str(input('Enter the GitHub account you want to look up: '))\n",[134,857,858],{"class":136,"line":175},[134,859,850],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":849},[134,861,862],{"class":136,"line":188},[134,863,864],{},"r = requests.get(f'https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002F{username}\u002Fstarred')\n",[17,866,867,868,870,871,874,875,878],{},"Next up is writing to JSON. To make sure the request actually succeeded before we write anything, we add a check so we only write to the JSON file when the call comes back OK. One thing to watch out for here: the JSON that ",[31,869,33],{}," hands back is a Python ",[31,872,873],{},"list",", which Python understands, so we have to process it before saving it to a ",[31,876,877],{},".json"," file:",[125,880,882],{"className":835,"code":881,"language":837,"meta":130,"style":130},"import requests\nimport json\n\nusername = str(input('Enter the GitHub account you want to look up: '))\n\nr = requests.get(f'https:\u002F\u002Fapi.github.com\u002Fusers\u002F{username}\u002Fstarred')\n\nif r.status_code == 200:\n  starList = open('starList.json', 'w+')\n  starList.write(json.dumps(r.json()))\n  starList.close()\nelse:\n  print('Something went wrong while fetching the API.')\n",[31,883,884,888,893,897,901,905,909,913,918,923,928,933,938],{"__ignoreMap":130},[134,885,886],{"class":136,"line":137},[134,887,844],{},[134,889,890],{"class":136,"line":144},[134,891,892],{},"import json\n",[134,894,895],{"class":136,"line":161},[134,896,850],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":849},[134,898,899],{"class":136,"line":175},[134,900,855],{},[134,902,903],{"class":136,"line":188},[134,904,850],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":849},[134,906,907],{"class":136,"line":201},[134,908,864],{},[134,910,911],{"class":136,"line":214},[134,912,850],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":849},[134,914,915],{"class":136,"line":227},[134,916,917],{},"if r.status_code == 200:\n",[134,919,920],{"class":136,"line":240},[134,921,922],{},"  starList = open('starList.json', 'w+')\n",[134,924,925],{"class":136,"line":253},[134,926,927],{},"  starList.write(json.dumps(r.json()))\n",[134,929,930],{"class":136,"line":266},[134,931,932],{},"  starList.close()\n",[134,934,935],{"class":136,"line":279},[134,936,937],{},"else:\n",[134,939,940],{"class":136,"line":292},[134,941,942],{},"  print('Something went wrong while fetching the API.')\n",[17,944,945],{},"And just like that, we've built a little tool that grabs the projects someone else has starred. Pretty simple, right? You could take it even further from here.",[17,947,948,949],{},"Today's code lives in this repo: ",[80,950,951],{"href":951,"rel":952},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fjavascript-to-python",[84],[12,954,956],{"id":955},"a-note-from-the-author","A note from the author",[17,958,959],{},"I used to always grab microwave meals from 7-11 for lunch or dinner. But recently I realised FamilyMart's microwave meals taste way better than 7-11's, and now I'm hooked on FamilyMart's stuff. Problem is, FamilyMart is so far from my place. QQ",[12,961,963],{"id":962},"about-the-bunnies","About the bunnies",[49,965,966,973,981,989],{},[52,967,968],{},[80,969,972],{"href":970,"rel":971},"https:\u002F\u002Ftailwindcss.tw",[84],"Tailwind CSS Taiwan official site",[52,974,975,980],{},[80,976,979],{"href":977,"rel":978},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002Ftailwindcss.tw",[84],"Tailwind CSS Taiwan"," (Facebook page)",[52,982,983,988],{},[80,984,987],{"href":985,"rel":986},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002Fgroups\u002Ftailwindcss.taiwan",[84],"The Bunny Cult × Tailwind CSS Taiwan"," (Facebook group)",[52,990,991],{},[80,992,995],{"href":993,"r